-- Indian shares fall for 2nd session on Fed worries; blue-chips drop
-- By Indulal PM
-- Wed Sep 10, 2014 06:08AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, Sept 10 (Reuters) - Indian shares fell for a second consecutive session on Wednesday, retreating from record highs hit early this week, as worries that the Federal Reserve would raise interest rates sooner than expected hit blue-chips such as Infosys.

The benchmark BSE index <.BSESN> provisionally closed down 0.76 percent at 27,057.41, while the broader NSE index <.NSEI> ended 0.63 percent lower at 8,101.70.